Description: Fragment of a marble leaf moulding on a very high relief with high piping around. On the light grey and partly glazed marble no traces of paint were found.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (Attributed by Petrie to the 'second temple of Apollo'.)
Curator's comments: Fragment belongs together with B 421, B 423 and B 424 to a leaf moulding. Fragments B 410, B 411 and B 422 build the corner piece, whilst this fragment is probably the internal part. Published (Koenigs 2007, 332 Cat. 25; Petrie 1886, Pl. 14,7; Altekamp 137ff. No. 2; 548 Fig. 125)
